description:
Contents include:

The Reunion (comic strip): While delivering a parcel to a trio of mad scientists, Bill accidentally has his mind switched with a mouse.

And For My Next Invention (illustrated text story): In which Graeme invents a variety of high-tech trandem bikes in a bid to solve the city of Grimsdyke-by-Sea's pollution problems.

All A'Bored (comic strip): The Goodies are hired to cheer up Lord Bored by running a nightclub for him, but come into conflict with the robot Bulboso.

Hiram's Holiday (comic strip): While babysitting spoilt Texan baby Hiram, the Goodies inadvertently use a magic lamp which sends them all to ancient Egypt, where the Goodies fall foul of the child Pharaoh Atishooma.

Sureshots Steal Show (illustrated text story): The Goodies use circus animals to form their own football team, the Breezy Sureshots, and go on to win the F.A. Cup.

Sprechen Sie Serbo-Croat? (comic strip): The Goodies provide a letter translating service, GoodTrans, but are hampered by their inability to speak any language other than their native English (plus the Spanish words for "Do you have any other flavours of ice cream?").

The Hobbymobile (illustrated text story): Graeme creates a Hobbymobile to keep his friends amused, but Tim's inability to choose which hobby to pursue causes problems, and Bill's desire to play music causes the Hobbymobile to turn him into a hugely noisy one-man-band.

Safari So Goodie (comic strip): When their attempts to sell hamburgers proves unsuccessful, the Goodies go to Africa, hoping that market will prove more welcoming, but end up tackling two criminals posing as a ghost.
Reprints some of the Cor!! Goodies strips, alongside games and features.
